# Design tokens (SCSS)

**Source of truth**: `styles/_tokens.scss` (imported as `@use 'tokens'` from `styles/index.scss`).

## Content max-width

Never add new magic `max-width: Nrem` for copy/layout columns. Use CSS variables:

| Token | rem | Typical use |
|-------|-----|-------------|
| `--rc-content-max-tight` | 32 | Short blurbs |
| `--rc-content-max-narrow` | 36 | Section intros |
| `--rc-content-max-comfort` | 38 | Quotes, asides |
| `--rc-content-max-reading` | 40 | Hero leads, grid headers |
| `--rc-content-max-teaser` | 44 | Hero stage copy |
| `--rc-content-max-wide` | 72 | Blog/article shell |
| `--rc-content-max-marketing` | 76 | Full landing shell |

Landing aliases (inside `.landing` only): `--landing-max` → marketing; `--landing-content-max` → wide.

```scss
// ❌
max-width: 40rem;
// ✅
max-width: var(--rc-content-max-reading);
```

Local UI constraints (e.g. `min(16rem, calc(100vw - …))` for a tuner pane) are OK when not part of the content scale.

## Breakpoints

Use `$rc-bp-*` from `_tokens.scss` — **not** raw `768px`, `900px`, etc.

```scss
@use 'tokens' as *;

@media (min-width: $rc-bp-md) { … }
@media (max-width: rc-below($rc-bp-lg)) { … }
```

Scale: `$rc-bp-2xs` 380 · `$rc-bp-xs` 420 · `$rc-bp-sm` 480 · `$rc-bp-md` 768 · `$rc-bp-lg` 900 · `$rc-bp-xl` 1024.

## Mixins (`styles/_mixins.scss`)

- `@include content-panel` — bordered utility panels
- `@include page-eyebrow` — uppercase caps label (blog, FAQ, roadmap, utility heroes)
- `@include page-eyebrow-pill` — **app landing hero only** (pill + accent fill)
- `@include tinted-icon-chip($bg, $fg, $border)` — icon chips; prefer `var(--accent-a*)` / `var(--accent-11)` for brand chrome

## Color discipline

- **Brand chrome**: `var(--accent-*)` (theme-driven per route)
- **Status / neutral UI**: `--rc-semantic-success|warning|neutral` — not per-section rainbow hues
- **Text**: `--rc-text-primary`, `--rc-text-secondary`
- Avoid new hardcoded hex brand colors (e.g. `#ffe066`, one-off jade/blue for decorative icons)

## Prose

Long-form utility pages: extend `.site-prose` in `styles/prose.scss`, not ad-hoc heading margins in page SCSS.
